Eat a balanced diet rich in antioxidants: Eating a healthy and balanced diet that includes plenty of antioxidant-rich foods is one of the best ways to reduce oxidative stress and support overall health. Examples of antioxidant-rich foods include fruits and vegetables like blueberries, cherries, spinach, kale, and broccoli. (Harvard Health Publishing, 2020)  2. Exercise regularly: Regular physical activity helps reduce oxidative stress as well as improving overall health, reducing cholesterol, and helping to prevent chronic disease. (Mayo Clinic, 2020) 3. Limit exposure to environmental toxins: Limiting exposure to environmental toxins is important for reducing oxidative stress and protecting your health. Examples of toxins to limit include cigarette smoke, air pollution, and other toxic chemicals. (Healthline, 2019)  4. Limit alcohol intake: This is an important one as alcohol can cause oxidative damage to the body. Limiting your alcohol intake is key to reducing oxidative stress and protecting your health. (NIH, 2020) 5. Get adequate sleep: A lack of sleep has been linked to increased oxidative stress. Aim to get 7-9 hours of quality sleep per night in order to reduce oxidative stress. (Mayo Clinic, 2020)  6. Reduce stress: Stress causes an increase in free radicals and oxidative stress. Practicing stress reduction techniques like meditation, yoga, deep breathing, and mindfulness can help reduce stress and reduce oxidative stress. (Harvard Health Publishing, 2020)"}}
